extends layout

block content
  .primary-container-hero
    .hero-card
      .hero-text
        h1.hero.white Navigate and improve inclusion in your workplace.
        h4.hero.white Skipper is the easiest way to quantitatively measure unconscious bias and engagement in teams.
        a.hero-button(href='beta.html') Try Skipper
      .hero-image
        img.flex(src=imgpath + 'home-hero.png')

    .container.moat
      .row
        .col-md-4
          .card.centered
            .tape
              img(src=imgpath + 'home-yellowtape.png')
            h2 Features
            h4 Insights and recommendations are delivered with analytics.
            .card-icon
              img(src="images/home-bottle.png")
        
        .col-md-4
          .card.centered
            .tape
              img(src="images/home-yellowtape.png")
            h2 Features
            h4 Insights and recommendations are delivered with analytics.
            .card-icon
              img(src="images/home-anchor.png")

        .col-md-4
          .card.centered
            .tape
                img(src="images/home-yellowtape.png")
            h2 Features
            h4 Insights and recommendations are delivered with analytics.
            .card-icon
              img(src="images/home-compass.png")

  .background-blue.full-width-bg.centered
    .primary-container
      h1.hero.white Understand your people.
      h4.white Using natural language understanding, community structure analysis, and linguistic inquiry methods, we examine social interactions over company messaging platforms to aggregates analyses on your team’s communication and provide recommendations accordingly through a web app. 
      img.large(src="images/home-demo.png")

  .primary-container
    .container
      .row.moat
        .centered.child-width.display-hide
            img.medium(src="images/home-features1.png")
        .col-md-6
          .feature-text
            h1 Wide platform support.
            h4 Whether you're on Slack, Hipchat, Mattermost, or your own company messaging platform, we should be able to help you run our specially designed algorithm on your own computers. 
        .col-md-6
          .centered.child-width.float-right
            img.medium(src="images/home-features1.png")
      
      .row.moat
        .col-md-6
          .centered.child-width.float-left
            img.medium(src="images/home-features2.png")
        
        .col-md-6
          .feature-text
            h1 Sort your team.
            h4 See how your communication differs from one group to another  based on gender, race, and role. 

      .row.moat
        .centered.child-width.display-hide
            img.medium(src="images/home-features3.png")
        .col-md-6
          .feature-text
            h1 Culture, visualized.
            h4 See different analyses on your team, such as sentiment and engagement.  
        .col-md-6
          .centered.child-width.float-right
            img.medium(src="images/home-features3.png")

      .row.moat
        .col-md-6
          .centered.child-width.float-left
            img.medium(src="images/home-features4.png")
        
        .col-md-6
          .feature-text
            h1 Make sense of the numbers.
            h4 Get quick explanations about how we calculate the numbers and why they matter. 

  .background-dark-blue.full-width-bg
    .primary-container(style="max-width: 750px;")
      h1(style='max-width: 600px; float:left; margin-top: 40px;').white Results, anchored in research.
      h4(style='max-width: 600px; float:left; margin-bottom: -40px;').white.narrow We’ve included some of the foundational papers informing our findings here. If you’re interested in a specific area of our tech, feel free to contact us for the research that we’ve developed it from.
    img.full(src='images/home-research-header.png' style='margin-bottom: -10px;')
  .background-sand.full-width-bg  
    .primary-container
      +article(
      'Journal of Language and Social Psychology', 
      'The Psychological Meaning of Words: LIWC and Computerized Text Analysis Methods', 
      'Yla R. Tausczik and James W. Pennebaker', 
      'This paper explains Linguistic Inquiry and Word Count, a text analysis program that counts words in psychologically meaningful categories. LIWC can detect attentional focus, emotionality, social relationships, thinking styles, and individual differences.'
